import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Deaths', data=data, hue='Entity', legend='full')
    plt.title('What is the trend of deaths over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Entity', loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='Entity', y='Deaths', data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths across different entities?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Entity')
    plt.ylabel('Deaths')
    plt.legend(title='Entities', loc='upper right', labels=data['Entity'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    average_deaths = data['Deaths'].mean()

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Deaths', data=data)
    plt.axhline(y=average_deaths, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Deaths: {average_deaths:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average number of deaths per year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Deaths')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year
    data['Deaths_pct_change'] = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].pct_change() * 100
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Deaths_pct_change', hue='Entity', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the percentage change in deaths over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Percentage Change in Deaths')
    plt.legend(title='Entity', loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
